# ============================================================================
# S.P.I.D.E.R. — privacy-first .gitignore
# The repo ships the SYSTEM (prompts, templates, reference). It must NEVER ship
# anyone's personal career data or generated outputs. Everything personal lives
# under workspace/ and is ignored. When in doubt, it does not get committed.
# ============================================================================

# --- Personal workspaces & all generated output (the #1 rule) ----------------
workspace/*
!workspace/.gitkeep
!workspace/README.md

# --- The author's own private career system (never publish) -------------------
koushik-docs/
../koushik-docs/
*koushik-docs*

# --- Anyone's source documents (resumes, LinkedIn exports, cover letters) -----
# NOTE: patterns are case-insensitive on macOS (core.ignorecase) but NOT on Linux, so spell out the
# common case variants explicitly — otherwise a `Resume.pdf` slips through on a contributor's Linux box.
*.resume.*
*-resume.md
*-resume.pdf
*-resume.docx
*[Rr]esume*.pdf
*[Rr]esume*.docx
*[Rr]esume*.md
[Rr]esume.*
*[Cc][Vv]*.pdf
*[Cc][Vv]*.docx
linkedin-data/
linkedin_extracted/
Basic_LinkedIn_Data*/
Complete_LinkedIn_Data*/
*.linkedin.zip
Connections.csv
messages.csv
Invitations.csv
Email Addresses.csv
Profile.csv
Positions.csv
Skills.csv
Endorsement*.csv

# --- Generated personal artifacts anywhere in the tree ------------------------
# These are unanchored so they apply in EVERY directory — including examples/,
# templates/, reference/, prompts/. The system's own files are named differently
# (master-resume-TEMPLATE.md, linkedin-analysis.TEMPLATE.html, 00-orchestrator.md,
# …) so they are never matched by these patterns and stay committed. Do NOT add a
# broad `!templates/**`-style re-include here — that re-opens the leak these close.
**/master-resume.md
**/signal.md
**/cover-letter.md
**/*-cover-letter.md
**/resume.md
**/*-resume.md
**/*-resume.pdf
**/*-resume.docx
**/*-resume-*.pdf
**/*-signal-*.pdf
**/*.print.html
**/application-log.md
**/job-queue.md
**/intake.md
**/resume-audit.md
**/network-map.md
**/answer-bank.md
**/answer-sheet.md
**/daily-briefing.md
**/linkedin-analysis.html
**/start-here.html
**/.spider-state.json

# --- The ONE committed fictional sample (everything in it is invented) --------
# Scoped, deliberate exception so strangers can inspect real-shaped output. Real
# runs NEVER go in examples/ — they go in workspace/ (ignored). DO NOT broaden
# this beyond examples/sample-run/ (that re-opens the personal-data leak).
!examples/sample-run/
!examples/sample-run/**
# …but never commit an input dump even inside the sample:
examples/sample-run/inputs/

# --- OS / editor / tooling cruft ----------------------------------------------
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
.idea/
.vscode/
*.swp
*~
.claude/settings.local.json
node_modules/
__pycache__/
*.log
# --- UI runtime artifacts ---
ui/.port

# --- Brand images: only commit art you have the rights to ----------------------
# images/ is ignored by default so stock/copyrighted/unverified art can't be
# published by accident. Allow-list each cleared (licensed or original) file.
images/*
!images/spider_unsplash.jpg
!images/spider_unsplash2.jpg
